    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "MICH\nEL\nTHE AIR FRANCE CARAVELLE JET, LATEST ACIIEVEMENT OF FRENCH\nAERONAUTIC ICINOLOGY, TAKES OFF FROM ORLY AIRPORT (Paris) FOR\nKHALDE AIRPORT, BEIRUT, NOVEMBER 2ND, INAUGURATING THE FIRST JET\nSERVICE TO TIE\nLEBANESE CAPITAL. THE ROUTE PARIS-BEIRUT VIA ROME\nIS 2,049 STATUTE MILES (Paris-Rome 689 miles and Rome-Beirut 1,360\nmiles). ROUND-TRIP FARES FROM NEW YORK TO BEIRUT ARE: $840.60\nECONOMY CLASS, AND $1334.90 FIRST CLASS.\nDISTINGUISHING FEATURES OF THE AIR FRANCE CARAVELIE JET ARE:\nPLACEMENT OF TIC JET PODS ON THE REAR FUSELAGE JUST FORWARD AND\nTHE EMPENNAGE\nBELOT THE EMPENNAGE (all pessengers ride forward of the jets in\nA SWEPT WING\ncomplete comfort and vibrationless quiet): A SWEPT WING OF PURE\nAERODYNAMIC DESIGN UNINCUMBERED BY JET PLACEMENT; TRIANGULAR WIN-\nDOWS FOR GREATER PASSENGER VIEW DOWNWARD, AND HIGHEST STRUCTURAL\n(tea-rose\nSTRENGTH (tea-rose tinted panes to soften ultra violet rays at\nhigh altitude). THIS 500 MPH JET ACCOMMODATES 20 FIRST CLASS AND\n55 TOURIST CLASS PASSENGERS."
